    hadithEnglish:
      'Narrated Abu Huraira: While the Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) was saying something in a gathering, a Bedouin came and asked him, When would the Hour (Doomsday) take place? Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) continued his talk, so some people said that Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) had heard the question, but did not like what that Bedouin had asked. Some of them said that Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) had not heard it. When the Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) finished his speech, he said, Where is the questioner, who inquired about the Hour (Doomsday)? The Bedouin said, I am here, O Allahs Apostle . Then the Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) said, When honesty is lost, then wait for the Hour (Doomsday). The Bedouin said, How will that be lost? The Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) said, When the power or authority comes in the hands of unfit persons, then wait for the Hour (Doomsday.)',
