    hadithEnglish:
      'Narrated Nafi`: `Abdullah bin `Umar said: A man got up in the mosque and said: O Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) At which place you order us that we should assume the Ihram? Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) replied, The residents of Medina should assure the Ihram from Dhil-Hulaifa, the people of Syria from Al-Juhfa and the people of Najd from Qarn. Ibn `Umar further said, The people consider that Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) had also said, The residents of Yemen should assume Ihram from Yalamlam.  Ibn `Umar used to say, I do not: remember whether Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) had said the last statement or not?',
