      'Narrated Anas: It was the time for prayer, and those whose houses were near got up and went to their people (to perform ablution), and there remained some people (sitting). Then a painted stove pot (Mikhdab) containing water was brought to Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam)s The pot was small, not broad enough for one to spread ones hand in; yet all the people performed ablution. (The sub narrator said, We asked Anas, How many persons were you? Anas replied We were eighty or more). (It was one of the miracles of Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam)).',
