      'Narrated Ibn `Abbas: The Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) once passed by two graves and said, These two persons are being tortured not for a major sin (to avoid). One of them never saved himself from being soiled with his urine, while the other used to go about with calumnies (to make enmity between friends). The Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) then took a green leaf of a date-palm tree, split it into (pieces) and fixed one on each grave. They said, O Allahs Apostle! Why have you done so? He replied, I hope that their punishment might be lessened till these (the pieces of the leaf) become dry. (See the footnote of Hadith 215).',
