    hadithEnglish:
      'Narrated Ubaidullah Al-Khaulani: I heard `Uthman bin `Affan saying, when people argued too much about his intention to reconstruct the mosque of Allahs Messenger (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam), You have talked too much. I heard the Prophet (sallallahu alaihi wa sallam) saying, Whoever built a mosque, (Bukair thought that `Asim, another sub-narrator, added, Intending Allahs Pleasure), Allah would build for him a similar place in Paradise. ',
